<item>
            <title>[SPARK-22442] Schema generated by Product Encoder doesn&apos;t match case class field name when using non-standard characters</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-22442</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Product encoder encodes special characters wrongly when field name contains certain nonstandard characters.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example for:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;case class MyType(`field.1`: String, `field 2`: String)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;we will get the following schema&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;root&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&apos;table-wrap&apos;&gt;
&lt;table class=&apos;confluenceTable&apos;&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;&amp;#8211; field$u002E1: string (nullable = true)&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;&amp;#8211; field$u00202: string (nullable = true)&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a consequence of this issue a DataFrame with the correct schema can&apos;t be converted to a Dataset using .as&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;MyType&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
