                            <comment id="16239815" author="viirya" created="Mon, 6 Nov 2017 01:57:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I tried on latest master branch. It can work with &lt;tt&gt;as&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;MyType&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
scala&amp;gt; val df = Seq(MyType(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;a&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;b&quot;&lt;/span&gt;), MyType(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;c&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;d&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)).toDF
df: org.apache.spark.sql.DataFrame = [field$u002E1: string, field$u00202: string]
scala&amp;gt; df.as[MyType].collect
res7: Array[MyType] = Array(MyType(a,b), MyType(c,d))
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="16239821" author="mikelsanvi" created="Mon, 6 Nov 2017 02:03:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yes, that will work but it wont work for the correct schema that will be inferred if you read directly from json:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;spark.read.json(path).as&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;MyType&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;it won&apos;t work because the inferred schema will be&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;field.1: string, field 2: string&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
